The paper focuses on image restoration, specifically removing impulse noise, which is a common problem in computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also proposes a new sparse optimization method, which falls under the category of information theory (cs.IT) and machine learning (cs.LG). The method is applied to image denoising and deblurring, which are topics in multimedia (cs.MM) and signal processing (cs.SI).
